title: 820-00165 fan spins for 5 seconds then off
message:
Noticed minor corrosion on the clock chip so replaced and have new results. When board first powers on it only uses 339 miliamps for about 20 seconds before turning off but now it turns back on and at starters using 330 amps again but then stays continuously running between 500-600 miliamps. No image on internal or external still.

Do you still need all of those voltages or could this be a bios issue?

title: 820-00165 fan spins for 5 seconds then off
message:
You can try new BIOS, but check first if you get all voltages, including VCORE.
Also test the board alone, disconnecting LIO flex and other devices.
